Node "Osw_6_13b_3"
notes "Here endeth the forth argument. Increment the local variable Osw_Euth_Arg_4 by 1.\nDr. Oswald has pointed out that, not only do patients suffer from Sandover's increased background radiation levels, relatives who are emotionally tied to them do too."
is_wtg = false
{
NPCText "Assuming those relatives were perfectly healthy when the patient was first admitted to hospital, if they were to stay in Sandover, would they be in the same shape in twelve months' time? You see, the current system is a vicious circle where the sick get sicker, and where they often take their relatives with them."
      options {
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "I see. What other arguments do you have?" linkto "Osw_6_15"  notes ""
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Let me ask you about something else instead." linkto "Osw_9"  notes ""
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Maybe we should talk about this another time. Goodbye." linkto "done"  notes ""
              }
}
Node "Osw_6_13c"
notes ""
is_wtg = false
{
NPCText "Take Fran, for example. What I had to do was a tragedy, but you and I both know she wouldn't have seen the year out. Let's not forget Connor, though. Now that his poor mother's suffering has come to an end, there is nothing tying him to Sandover any more."
      options {
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "[MORE]" linkto "Osw_6_14"  notes ""
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Let me ask you about something else instead." linkto "Osw_9"  notes ""
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Maybe we should talk about this another time. Goodbye." linkto "done"  notes ""
              }
}
Node "Osw_6_14"
notes "Here endeth the forth argument. Increment the local variable Osw_Euth_Arg_4 by 1.\nDr. Oswald has pointed out that, not only do patients suffer from Sandover's increased background radiation levels, relatives who are emotionally tied to them do too."
is_wtg = false
{
NPCText "Connor is a fairly healthy young man. If he were to stay in Sandover, would he be in the same shape in twelve months' time, though? You see, the current system is a vicious circle where the sick get sicker, and where they often take their relatives with them."
      options {
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "I see. What other arguments do you have?" linkto "Osw_6_15"  notes ""
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Let me ask you about something else instead." linkto "Osw_9"  notes ""
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Maybe we should talk about this another time. Goodbye." linkto "done"  notes ""
              }
}
Node "Osw_6_15"
notes ""
is_wtg = false
{
NPCText "I already administer mercy killings occasionally and, of course, only when absolutely necessary. However, until Alexander grasps the nettle and makes the practice legal, and whilst my most vocal opponents condemn it, there's always going to be a sense that it's somehow wrong."
      options {
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "[MORE]" linkto "Osw_6_16"  notes ""
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Let me ask you about something else instead." linkto "Osw_9"  notes ""
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Maybe we should talk about this another time. Goodbye." linkto "done"  notes ""
              }
}
Node "Osw_6_16"
notes "Here endeth the fifth and final argument. Increment the local variable Osw_Euth_Arg_5 by 1.\nDr. Oswald has pointed out that many of his terminally ill patients turn down the option of euthanasia because they think it is morally wrong."
is_wtg = false
{
NPCText "Contrary to what people in other towns in the wastes may think, the majority of Sandover's inhabitants are decent, moral people. For years, many of my terminal patients, in spite of how much pain they were in, or that they had no hope of surviving, denied themselves a merciful end simply because they saw euthanasia as a grubby and immoral practice."
      options {
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "[MORE]" linkto "Osw_6_17"  notes ""
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Let me ask you about something else instead." linkto "Osw_9"  notes ""
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Maybe we should talk about this another time. Goodbye." linkto "done"  notes ""
              }
}
Node "Osw_6_17"
notes ""
is_wtg = false
{
NPCText "This is why the current state of affairs can't go on. For the reasons I've given so far, if you forced me to hazard a guess at the number of patients that die an unpleasant death, where they could have been offered a merciful way out, I'd say approximately 70-75% of all fatalities in this hospital fall into that category."
      options {
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "I see. What else can you tell me about your viewpoint?" linkto "Osw_6_18"  notes ""
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Let me ask you about something else instead." linkto "Osw_9"  notes ""
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Maybe we should talk about this another time. Goodbye." linkto "done"  notes ""
              }
}
Node "Osw_6_18"
notes ""
is_wtg = false
{
NPCText "I think I've covered the most obvious points. I'm glad to have met someone who has kept an open mind regarding the subject. Now, is there anything else? As you probably appreciate given what we've just discussed, I really must get back to my patients."
      options {
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Can I ask you a question about something else?" linkto "Osw_9"  notes ""
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "No, I won't take up any more of your time. Goodbye." linkto "done"  notes ""
              }
}
Node "Osw_7_1a"
notes "The Osw_7_* path is where the PC can offer to help out in the hospital, as per the quest of the same name (see wiki for details).\n"
is_wtg = false
{
